Ming Vase Fetches Record HK$169 Million at Sotheby’s Art Sale

-- B y   J a s m i n e   W a n g
-- 
2011-10-05T08:10:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-05/ming-vase-fetches-record-hk-169-million-at-sotheby-s-art-sale.html
A blue and white imperial vase from
the Ming Dynasty was sold for HK$168.66 million at a Sotheby’s
auction today in  Hong Kong , the company said in an e-mailed
statement.  The price, which compares with a pre-sale estimate of HK$80
million to HK$120 million, was the highest paid for Ming Dynasty
porcelain, Sotheby’s said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jasmine Wang in Hong Kong at 
 jwang513@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Regan at 
 jregan19@bloomberg.net  